
[1]hymn

   HYMN, n. hym. [L. hymnus; Eng. hum.]song or ode in honor of God, and
   among pagans, in honor of some deity. A hymn among christians is a
   short poem,composed for religious service, or a song of joy and praise
   to God. The word primarily expresses the tune,but it is used for the
   ode or poem.

   And when the had sung a hymn, they went out to the mount of Olives.
   Matt.26.

       HYMN, v.t. hym. To praise in song; to worship by singing hymns.

   1. To sing; to celebrate in song. They hymn their maker's praise.

               HYMN, v.i. hym. To sing in praise or adoration.
